reviewText: Even though this video is only 15 minutes, it would be impossible to expand it further without distorting the touchingly beautiful story. The photography was incredible, the film itself, poignant. That said, the price to buy should not be so high, but it is a good film that warms your heart. The young actor who plays the young boy is magnificent. YOU WILL WANT TO WATCH THIS OVER AND OVER AGAIN!!
summary: Touches Your Soul! A Must See! Tugs At The Heart For Sure!

reviewText: Short, but sweet. It seems a little pricey for such a short movie, but I imagine they don't have the bulk discounts of big films.A great one to buy and watch as a family before game night or on a religious holiday or the Sabbath. Inspiring true story during early America.

reviewText: Though this is a short movie ( only about 15 minutes), it is very emotionally moving. It tells the story of a pioneer family where a miracle took place that changed the children's lives. It is a sweet story that is true or at least based on a true incident. It is interesting for both adults and children.
